About Me

I am currently a final-year PhD student in School of Data Science at Fudan University, under the advised of Prof. Xuening Zhu. I obtained my Bachelor’s Degree in Economics and Master’s Degree in Applied Statistics from School of Statistics at Renmin University of China. My research interest lies in Network Analysis, High-dimensional Statistics, Spatial Econometrics, and Statistical Machine Learning.

Education

  • 2016–2020, B.S. in Economics (Economic Statistics), School of Statistics, Renmin University of China.

Research Interests
